   Sean, all I can say is try it. A bug (which is
> what the books refer to)
> is a lot different then a bus. What I say is what I
> have tested and
> experienced myself. I have a 1776 single port with a
> PICT 34 on it and found
> I had much better low end with a stock bus exhaust
> then a header. Also think
> about it. A beetle has 2 tailpipes, a bus has only
> one. VW must have tested
> the exhaust and determined that the single tip must
> have given the bus more
> bottom end to help move it. Same muffler, just 1 tip
> verses 2.
> 
> Ronnie
